## My Personal Snipmate Snippets

Because of butthurt for unused mess from `vim-snippets`. It's my very own
very imho very snippets. Don't hate me if I don't respecting for your opinion :D

Based on [honza/vim-snippets](https://github.com/honza/vim-snippets).

## Installation

```vim
" # Snippets
Bundle 'MarcWeber/vim-addon-mw-utils'
Bundle 'tomtom/tlib_vim'
Bundle 'garbas/vim-snipmate'
Bundle 'shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets'
```

## TOC

It's very useful to find a snippet if you need the one.

- [Global Snippets](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/_.snippets)
- [CSS Snippets](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/css.snippets)
- [HTML Snippets (just `html:5`)](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/html.snippets)
- [JavaScript Snippets](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/javascript.snippets)
- [Shell Snippets](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/sh.snippets)
- [Stylus Snippets](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/stylus.snippets)
- [Vim Snippets](https://github.com/shuvalov-anton/vim-snippets/blob/master/snippets/vim.snippets)
